title: Grateful Dead Live at Paramount Theater on 1977-10-01
description:
Set 1

Promised Land, They Love Each Other, Mexicali Blues, Dire Wolf, Cassidy, Deal, Passenger, Tennessee Jed, Minglewood Blues, Peggy-O, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Bertha-> Good Lovin', It Must Have Been The Roses, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Dancin' In The Streets-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Around & Around

reviews.review_text: Portland 77' A really strong show with some gr8 moments.Passenger is always awesome to hear.I believe the highlight in the first set was TMNS.The second set was pretty sweet with a nice Estimated)Eyes.Not fade away was nice with phil droppin some serious bombs.Over all a tight performance but there is alot better from fall 77'.Still i would recommend checkin' this show out.Sound quality is excellent in my opinion but it a Miller transfer.
